quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  28,44,"And you<sup>sg </sup>were not on the western side<i>(of the Mount) </i>when We decreed the command to Moses, nor were you<sup>sg </sup>of the witnesses."
  28,45,"Yet We established many generations{1}, then the ages became seemingly long. Nor were you among the people of Midian, reading Our signs{2}to them; but We have been sending emissaries.",1:[After Moses.],2:[The Arabic word used is <i>ayat</i> (singular <i>ayah</i>). <i>Ayah</i> means ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an, like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose. Each such unit is considered a ‘sign’ from God.]
  28,46,"Nor were you by the side of Mount Tûr when We called out. Rather, it was a mercy from your Lord so that you may warn a people to whom no warner had come before you, that perhaps they would remind themselves."
  28,47,"And<i>(We have sent you as a messenger) </i>lest a calamity befall them as a result of what their hands have put forth, and they say, “Our Lord, if only You had sent us a messenger, we would have followed Your signs and been among the believers.”"
  28,48,"But when the truth came to them from Our Providence, they said, “If only he was given the like of what was given to Moses.” Did they not deny what was given to Moses in the past? They said, “Two works{1}of sorcery{2}, backing one another.” And they said, “We deny both.”",1:[The Qur'an and the Torah.],2:[Qira’at: All except for Asem, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “Two sorcerers, backing…”]
  28,49,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Then bring a scripture from Allah more conducive to guidance than both of them and I will follow it, if you<sup>pl </sup>are truthful.”"
  28,50,"But if they do not respond to you<sup>sg </sup>, know that they only follow their whims. And who is more misguided than one who follows his own whim without guidance from Allah? Indeed, Allah does not guide the unjust people."
